                            <layoutDesc>
                                <layout style="vertical" rend="arris_up">From the drawing by Hitchcock and Macalister's (1945, 136) description, the inscription appears to take up two angles with the first word described as <q>on an angle turned inward, inaccessible except to the fingers on my first visit; and now still more so, for an accumulation of silt has in the interval buried everything except the final N.</q> According to Cuppage (1986, no. 285), the inscription occupies both angles on the E side of the stone but a reassessment of Macalister's readings of the inscriptions was not possible.</layout>
                            </layoutDesc>
                        </objectDesc>
                        <handDesc>
                            <handNote>Macalister (1945, 136) doesn't mention the execution type of this inscription. We have no information on the appearance of the characters. Hitchcock's drawing is not detailed enough to be helpful in this regard.<height/>
                            </handNote>
